  "output": "Confirmed via fresh scan + earlier session today. Findings below, ranked by impact.\n\n## 1. N+1 Query Patterns\n\n**`ReportRepository+FinancialStatements.swift:183-200`** — `balanceSheet()` loops accounts, calls `signedOpeningBalance()` per account; each miss triggers own `movementTotals()` query.\nFix: batch `movementTotals(for: raws.map(\\.0))` once, lookup from dict.\n\n**`AccountTreeCache.swift:58-67`** — `reload()` maps ledgers through `signedOpeningBalance()` one at a time. Runs on every tree reload.\nFix: same batch-first pattern.\n\n**`VoucherService.swift:1164-1175`** — `loadAccounts(ids:)` loops `accountRepo.findById(id)` per id instead of `IN (...)`.\nFix: add `AccountRepository.findByIds(_:)`.\n\n**`VoucherService.swift:1079-1085`** (6 call sites: 284, 397, 510, 576, 702, 772) — `markAccountsUsed` loops `markUsed()` per account even though `markUsedBatch(_:)` already exists at `AccountRepository.swift:258`.\nFix: swap loop for existing batch call. Free win, zero new code.\n\n**`ItemInvoiceService.swift:93-111`** — `post()` loops `inventoryRepo.findItemById()` per line item.\nFix: batch-fetch all itemIds before loop.\n\n**`InventoryService.swift:474-483`** — `republishAuthoritativeValuation` issues one `UPDATE` per stock movement on backdated recompute.\nFix: multi-row `UPDATE...CASE` or single batched statement.\n\n**`BankReconciliationService.swift:57-59`** — `importStatement` calls `assertDateOpen()` per entry, 2 queries each (FY lookup + lock check), even when entries share FY.\nFix: resolve distinct FYs once, validate per unique year.\n\n**`LedgerLineRepository.swift:23-44`, `VoucherItemLineRepository.swift:20-46`, `BOMRepository.swift:33-51`** — methods named `insertBatch` loop single-row `INSERT`s.\nFix: real multi-VALUES insert.\n\n**`FinancialYearOpeningBalanceRepository.swift:74-96`** — `replaceForFinancialYear` loops one insert per ledger on FY carry-forward (hundreds of rows).\nFix: same multi-row insert.\n\n## 2. Unnecessary Re-renders\n\n**`AccountPicker.swift:147-170`** — `sortedAccounts`/`filteredAccounts` are plain computed props, re-sort/filter full list on every access from `body`, popover, `move()`, `pickSelected()`.\nFix: cache in `@State`, recompute only `onChange(of: accounts/query)`.\n\n**`AccountsView.swift:142-154`** — `orderedGroups` rebuilds parent dict + recursive DFS every render, even for unrelated keystrokes/paging.\nFix: cache in view model, invalidate only on group reload.\n\n**`AccountsViewModel.swift:64`** — `reload()` refetches `groups` every debounced keystroke/page change, though group tree changes rarely.\nFix: fetch groups once per company, reuse.\n\n## 3. Caching Gaps\n\n**`GSTService.swift`** — no cache at all (unlike `ReportService.ReportCache`). `GSTViewModel.reload()` hits `summary()` + `buildReturn()` on every date-range change.\nFix: give `GSTService` same change-token cache as `ReportService`.\n\n**`ReportService.swift:81-109`** — `gstSummary`, `dayBook`, `outstanding`, `stockValuation`, `cashFlow`, `stockAgeing` bypass `ReportCache` entirely; only `ledger`/`trialBalance`/`profitAndLoss`/`balanceSheet` cached.\nFix: route through `Self.cache.value/store` same as others.\n\n**`ReportService.swift:37-38,48-49,62-63,73-74`** — `changeToken()` computed twice per cache miss (once inside `value(for:)`, again for `store()`).\nFix: return token alongside cache-miss result, reuse.\n\n## 4. Memory Leaks\n\nNone found. App is `@Observable`, no `Timer.scheduledTimer`, no `.sink`. Long-lived closures either capture only locals or use `[weak self]` correctly (`AccountsViewModel.reload/disable`). `KeyboardMonitor` holds router `weak`. Clean.\n\n## 5. Redundant Computations\n\n**`GSTService.swift:63-64`** — `GSTViewModel.reload()` calls `summary()` then `buildReturn()`, which internally re-calls `summary()`. Same aggregate query runs twice per refresh.\nFix: compute `summary` once, pass into `buildReturn(summary:)`.\n\n**`BankReconciliationService.swift:96-119`** — `reconcile()` does `vouchers.first(where:)` inside `for s in statement`, O(n·m) scan, recomputes `CheckedMath` per pair every run.\nFix: pre-sort/bucket vouchers by date/amount once outside loop.\n\nAlso flagged but stale: `AccountTreeCache` never invalidated on voucher post → stale balances shown until manual reload (separate correctness bug, not perf, but worth a ticket).\n\n**Quick wins (near-zero risk, do first):** `markAccountsUsed` swap to `markUsedBatch` (already exists), GST double-`summary()` call, `changeToken` double-query.\n",
